 year.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe are looking forward to celebrating the 10th Anniversary of this great idea with you all in New York City. Please submit your ideas, experiences, research, what have you, and join us.\r\n<h3>IMPORTANT DATES</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Submission of Extended-Abstract – March 14th, 2014</li>\r\n	<li>Upload your one page submission to</li>\r\n	<li>Acceptance notification – May 9th, 2014</li>\r\n	<li>Full paper draft – June 13th, 2014</li>\r\n	<li>Final paper – August 27th, 2014</li>\r\n	<li>In addition to Papers, EPIC 2014 will accept other types of submissions and participations: namely, Pecha-Kucha, Salons, Workshops, Doctoral &amp; Masters Colloquium, and Artifacts. More information about them will be sent out shortly.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>So, save the date</h3>\r\nAs you know, EPIC 2014 will be in New York on September 7-10, 2014. Are these dates in your calendar?\r\n<h3>SHARE THE NEWS</h3>\r\nOn twitter? Share your conversations by simply including this #EPIC2014 on your EPIC tweets!\r\n\r\nOn Facebook? Visit our page <strong><a title=\"here\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/epiconference\">here</a></strong> and like it to stay up to date with the latest news.\r\n\r\nPlease help us spread the word, forward the call to anyone you think might be interested, like us on Facebook, tweet us... generally just \"activate those networks\".\r\n\r\nTill next time,\r\nyour Co-chairs – Timothy Malefyt &amp; Rogério de Paula','Call For Papers','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision-v1','','','2014-02-17 19:12:02','2014-02-17 19:12:02','',4,'http://powinteractive.pairserver.com/epic/?p=40',0,'revision','',0),(41,1,'2014-02-17 19:39:25','2014-02-17 19:39:25','Back in 2004, in a somewhat serendipitous encounter, two anthropologists from the industry realized the need for a forum to draw together their kinds and others as well. This was the inception of EPIC – the Ethnographic Praxis in the Industry Conference.\r\n\r\nTen years later, EPIC has become a confere