ented a paper or workshop, or been involved in the EPIC review process or have done volunteer work or committee work, or shown commitment to EPIC in some other way – EPIC would like to enable you to showcase your book at EPIC2014.\r\n\r\nWe would encourage authors to not only bring a stack of fliers with them (there will be a pin-up wall for that) but also a number of their books, which they are willing to sell. Sales will be up to each individual author. EPIC (the organization) will not be involved in any financial transactions. If you wish to have your book considered for the authors’ space, please send us the title with publication data, together with a few lines responding to the criteria listed above. Submit by <strong>April 30</strong> to Gitti Jordan (<a href=\"mailto:gitti.jordan@gmail.com\">gitti.jordan@gmail.com</a>).\r\n\r\nWe welcome your comments and suggestions for helping us make this a success. Please feel free to circulate the information about this exciting new opportunity for the authors and attendees at EPIC2014.','Call for Participation','','inherit','open','open','','57-revision-v1','','','2014-03-10 17:16:53','2014-03-10 17:16:53','',57,'http://powinteractive.pairserver.com/epic/?p=133',0,'revision','',0),(137,1,'2014-03-10 19:52:01','2014-03-10 19:52:01','<strong>WHO ATTENDS EPIC</strong>\r\n\r\nEach year, about 350-400 people come from all over for three days of panels, papers, workshops, Pecha Kucha, and multi-media displays. Our diverse attendees come from large technology companies and small design studios, universities and NGOs, advertising, finance, public policy and healthcare.\r\n\r\n<strong>WHO SUPPORTS EPIC</strong>\r\n\r\nWe welcome corporate and individual contributions at all levels.  Our sponsors are as diverse as our attendees and many sponsor year over year, demonstrating the benefit they have experienced from being part of our community.\r\n\r\n<strong>WHY YOU SHOULD SPONSOR EPIC</strong>\r\n\r\nSponsor EPIC 2014 and your don