p discussions.\r\n[/expand]\r\n<div class=\"grey-text\">Hosted by <strong>Anna Avrekh</strong>, User Experience Researcher, <strong>Kathy Baxter</strong>, Staff User Experience Researcher, and <strong>Bob Evans</strong>, Software Engineer, Google, Inc. </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n[expand title=\"You Can’t Be Serious?! – LEGO® Serious Play® - Serious Solution Crafting for Kids aged 3 to 103.\"]We all loved tinkering when were kids… but have you ever considered using colourful bricks as a serious business tool? Placing the experience at the heart of matters, we’re inviting participants to flex their haptic muscles; building metaphors, &amp; conjuring meaning through tactile story making. This invigorating, hands-on solution crafting won’t disappoint. So, don’t be surprised if you LEGO® of your inhibitions…[/expand]\r\n<div class=\"grey-text\">Hosted by <strong>Dörte Töllner</strong>, Founder and Managing Director and <strong>Cori Moore</strong>, Communications Strategist, Point-Blank International Marketing Research & Consultancy</div>\r\n\r\n[expand title=\"Studying In and Out: Linking Organizational and Consumer Ethnography\"]Consumer ethnographers are quite capable of describing and explaining the relationships among products, services, consumers, and customers when called upon to do so by a business client. But when we do not understand the organization’s culture, “silos,” internal power relationships, view of staff, and stakeholder dynamics, our understandings may not translate into meaningful responses. Come to this workshop to learn strategies for maximizing your impact with organizational leaders, while doing the work of understanding products, services, consumers, and customers!\r\n\r\nWe are two business anthropologists: one of us specializes in organizational-culture and change, and the other in global products, services, and markets. We introduce case material from a variety of industries in which organizations struggled to respond to emerging consumer preferences a